Yaroslav Faybishenko (fby@netcom.com) wrote:

: This maybe really a stupid thing to say, but why would you want to use a 
: cordless phone which encrypts the number you dial and your converstaion?
: That would only eliminate the people w/ the scanners.  Otherwise, this 
: system is equivalent to no encryption at all, since the conversation goes 
: un-encrypted through the phone lines, so anyone can still tap the phone 
: line and listen.

Eliminating the scanner problem IS an important step.  It is the easiest
way to snoop.

